# Vercel cost (Sheetomatic)

While production remains on **Vercel** (even temporarily), optimize **$** only in ways that keep UX fast and prod stable. Full playbook: `docs/VERCEL-COST-PLAYBOOK.md`. Pricing reference: https://vercel.com/pricing

## Hard constraints (never “save money” by doing these)

- Do **not** disable Fluid / cold-start prevention.
- Do **not** recommend Spend Management that **pauses** production — alerts only.
- Do **not** lower webhook or `leads-sync` `maxDuration` below what delivery/import needs (`vercel.json`).
- Do **not** remove product crons, tenant isolation, or `CRON_SECRET` checks.
- Do **not** suggest Hobby for commercial Sheetomatic production.

## Preferred savings (safe)

- **Shorter function time:** batch DB (no N+1 / huge parallel fan-out), early-exit idle crons, keep heavy Sheets work in `after()` / cron — not on the user-critical path.
- **Retries that prevent double traffic:** use `withDbRetry` on hot DB paths; fix “Connection closed” causes (pool + query shape), don’t ignore them.
- **Seats:** Viewer (free) vs Member ($20); only deployers need paid seats.
- **Add-ons off unless required:** SAML, HIPAA, Static IP, Flags Explorer, Preview suffix, Analytics Plus, Speed Insights, Observability Plus.
- **Builds:** avoid useless preview/build spam; don’t enable costly concurrency without need.
- **Images:** don’t gratuitously transform every asset via Image Optimization; use sized `public/` assets when transforms aren’t needed.
- **Region:** keep Fluid functions near the Postgres/Neon region (latency ↓ and CPU ↓).
- **Neon:** pooler URL on Vercel; avoid sleep/tiny DB that causes connection storms (retries burn Function $).

## When touching these areas, check the playbook

- `vercel.json` crons / `maxDuration`
- `/app/leads` load path and Sheets sync
- `next/image` usage on marketing or high-traffic UI
- New Vercel marketplace / analytics / observability products
- Deploy frequency and preview policy

## Longer term

Railway Pro single-platform path is documented in `docs/RAILWAY.md`. Until DNS cutover, **Vercel stays production** — cost work must not assume Railway is live.
